I also know some casters who did want the cloak for themselves, already had bards who would trade the scale for the cloak (and they had a right to do this ...Imho). <br>
<br>
As to who won the scale. I think the idea of CaWu was twisted in this case. While this person may be a great person normally( I don't know him/her) I remember the arguement he/she made...and it was stressed it was about how the cloak was a super item and he/she should be able to roll on it for the intention of getting a cloak. Thats the only thing that casts a cloud over the situtation. If it is going to a bard..fine...I may not like the way it happened...but its done ..and many things in this game are open to differing opinions. I just feel sorry for the bards that came and lost on the roll <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
The thing I DON'T want this to do is look negatively on the Drunks. They did an OUTSTANDING job. The raid was handled well, the loot was handled with some care ...and a want to be fair. The only thing they may be guilty of is being TOO nice and not trying to lay down the law. <br>
<br>
<br>
/mourn the bards who didn't get their scale<br>
/shrug the caster who won<br>
/CHEER the Drunks of Tunare <p><center>Phazy Daayz 52st lvl Disciple<center><br><center> EXILE<center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utulok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tulok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/1/01 10:06:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Drunks and friends.....</span><hr size=1> To Everyone concerned<br>
<br>
It would seem that a minor scandal has come out of our Vox Raid, it was never our intention that the White Scale be given to a players Alt, but unfortunately we have no control over where or how loot is used after its given out.  Our only wish was to be fair to all parties involved, both caster and bard.  This was our guilds first dragon raid and I'm afraid we were not nearly as clear on loot rules as we should have been, in the future this will of course be fixed.  I would like to thank everyone involved, our goal of slaying the dragon was accomplished and I hope you will all join us in future endeavors.<br>
<br>
Tinker<br>
Drunks of Tunare<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utypan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Typan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/1/01 10:12:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Drunks and friends.....</span><hr size=1> I blame Verant not only for making this scale which makes a caster cloak part of the bard epic, but for placing an epic piece on a level capped mob.  Making the Kunark version of her one of the toughest dragons out there doesn't help either.  <br>
<br>
My point is, either way...if casters win or bards win, the scale goes to a bard.  I have no doubts that this occurs at least 9 out of 10 times with the scale.  If a caster should happen to win, they either rerandom it to the present bards or trade it to a higher level bard who is no longer allowed to attend Vox raids.  <br>
<br>
The only reason people are attacking Faandeg is because he won it as a caster, and gave it to his own bard.  I want to see the white scale go to bards as well, and pretty much every time it drops...it does.  Either via winning the roll or via trade.  The WSDC isn't all that great anyways, gimme a Heiro any day.<br>
<br>
I'd be more angry at Verant for putting bards in this situation than at a bard for finding a way around it.  Thanks,<br>
<br>
Typan Kagonesti<br>
Wanderer of Tunare<br>
Legion of Heroes<br>
<br>
P.S.  All you bards out there that are leveling an alt to Vox raid level in hopes of winning a scale, best just stop now.  Apparently, people don't like your solution to this inane problem.<br>
<br>
P.P.S.  To the Drunks:  You are not at fault here, I'm sure the raid was executed wonderfully, and the loot was rolled as fairly as possible.  I'm glad to see you all doing so well, those in your guild that I've met are good people. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utypan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Typan</A> at: 5/1/01 10:18:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uimnnaru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>imnnaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/1/01 10:18:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Drunks and friends.....</span><hr size=1> You guys did an awesome not only running the raid, but also trying to be fair with the loot. Either one of my Chars would be more than happy to help you good people out anytime <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Imnnaru 50 Ranger <BR> Anaru 51 Cleric <BR> Children of the Mother Officer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucalculonbattlebow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calculon Battlebow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.flspot.com/loa/mb/loa_iconsm.gif WIDTH=29 HEIGHT=17 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Calculator</span><br>  Posts: 478<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/1/01 11:01:20 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.flspot.com/loa/mb/icons/ico_daedlee.gif width=75 height=84></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Drunks and friends.....</span><hr size=1> Easiest solution?  Faandeg should have contacted the Drunks prior to the raid and explained his situation.  He would have run the risk of them refusing his request to roll on the scale with all the other bards, but given their attitude towards epic help, I seriously doubt that would have been the case.  But that is in the past, hindsight is, as usual, much clearer.<br>
<br>
Now that the damage is done, I ask you...what damage was it?  Did he have a right to roll on the scale, alongside the other bards and casters?  Yes.  Did he roll under CaWU rules, stating that he would use and not trade away that scale?  Yes.  Did he fail to abide by those rules?  No, he's gonna use the scale himself, albeit for a slightly different purpose than another cleric would have done?  So was CaWU broken?  No.  Did the scale go to a deserving person?  Yes.  Did it go towards a noble goal?  Yes.  <br>
<br>
His only mistake was misleading the raid on how the loot he won would be used, but as long as you *do* use it, who cares.  Would you frown on someone passing a CaWU won item on to their twink once they got better?  In my opinion, he earned and deserves the scale, though... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarksydodymoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darksyd Odymoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/1/01 11:26:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Drunks and friends.....</span><hr size=1> What if he got a WDSC to give to his own cleric in exchange for the scale? Would that make the preceived situation better? I have no opinion one way or the other, just interjecting some questions. That would be the same as another person winning it and getting the cloak in trade. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 407<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/1/01 11:36:21 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae4.jpg height=158 width=119></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Drunks and friends.....</span><hr size=1> Here's my take from what I know.<br>
<br>
Bards on this server are a fairly tight bunch.  We try to help each other as best we can with songs, advice, epic help, etc.  I think there is nothing wrong with a Bard leveling up a caster and using said character to compete for a White Scale.  However, it needs to be done with full disclosure to the raid and the other Bards.<br>
<br>
What really irks me is if Faandeg had spoken with the other Bards on the raid and informed them of what he was doing, I can almost guarantee they would have given him an equal shot at the scale right alongside them.  The problem was Faandeg did not let others know.  Probably no one would have known if I had not talked to a Drunks member to determine who the winner was and if Katran had not posted that he got a tell from Faandeg.<br>
<br>
That is the real issue.  That the other Bards on the raid, and the raid in general, seems to have been deceived. I would really like to hear Faandeg's comments on this issue. <p><font size=2 face="Tempus Sans ITC, Verdana, Helvetica">
Kulanae Soulsease</font><br>
<font size=2 face="Helvetica">
Bardess of 56 seasons<br>
